  <refnamediv>
    <refname>rgb2hsv</refname>
    <refpurpose>Convert a RGB image to the equivalent HSV image</refpurpose>
  </refnamediv>


<refsynopsisdiv>
   <title>Syntax</title>
   <synopsis>
   HSV = rgb2hsv(RGB)
   
   </synopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsection>
   <title>Parameters</title>
   <variablelist>
   <varlistentry><term>RGB :</term>
      <listitem><para> A RGB image (matrix), the dimension of RGB should be M x N x 3 .</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   <varlistentry><term>HSV :</term>
      <listitem><para> Output image, which has the same size and type as RGB.</para></listitem></varlistentry>
   </variablelist>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Description</title>
   <para>
rgb2hsv convert a RGB image to the equivalent HSV image
   </para>
   <para>
Supported classes: INT8, UINT8, INT16, UINT16, INT32, DOUBLE.
   </para>
   <para>
</para>
</refsection>

<refsection>
   <title>Examples</title>
   <programlisting role="example"><![CDATA[
RGB = imread(fullpath(getIPCVpath() + "/images/baboon.png"));
HSV = rgb2hsv(RGB);
RGB = hsv2rgb(HSV);
imshow(RGB);

   ]]></programlisting>
</refsection>

